description:
“drop in for a no drop run!”

not set route, no set pace, just a common place to meet up and find company for your monday miles! start the week off right and join us at 6:00pm every first, second, and third monday of the month at the trailhead store! 

what to expect:
- 6:00pm gather & mingle
- 6:05 icebreaker & introductions 
- 6:10pm depart for run
- 7:00pm return to Brooks

there will be a leader there to guide anyone interested in a 4-6 mile route, but you’re also welcome to buddy up and do your own thing! monday nights are for getting what you need :)

this event is open to women, trans, and non-binary people who are comfortable in a space that centers the experiences of women. our only rule is that nobody runs alone ❤️

*4th/5th monday will typically be field trip runs at outside locations announced on the cowgill strava page
title: womxn run the herd

description:
join us for some early morning urban trail miles! meet at the Caffe Vita near Third Place Books in Seward and bring your headlamps! our route is 5 miles with 500ft of vert.

what to expect:
- 6:30am meet and mingle
- 6:35am introductions and icebreaker
- 6:40am begin run
- 7:30am ish finish run
- option to get coffee & hang post-run at Cafe Vita

this no-drop, biweekly Tuesday morning run is open to women, nonbinary, and trans people who are comfortable in a space that centers the experiences of women. our only rule is that nobody runs alone :)

*no drop means nobody will be  left to run by themselves. we will always adjust our paces to meet the needs of the group. Tuesday morning runs typically range anywhere from 9min/mile to 15min/mile pace
title: womxn run the herd: morning edition

description:
Saturday: We’ll be hosting an aid station for the Deception Pass 50k. See Slack for volunteering details.

Saturday night: Free & sheltered camping with a fire at Raymond’s family farm near Burlington (thanks Raymond!). See Slack for camping details.

Sunday: Meet at North Chuckanut TH Sunday morning for several route options exploring the Chuckanut area. Social post-run at GRUFF brewing. For all the routes be prepared with navigation!

The longest route runs ends at GRUFF Brewing! Please coordinate carpooling if wanting this option! Bring your ID since no minors are allowed at GRUFF brewing.
